description.narrative:
This project aims to improve poor and marginalized families, through increasing access to microcredit for small enterprise of womenin 3 districts of Nampula province. The project will also provide TA to the beneficiaries in desingn, implanting and monitoring projects. Activities will benefit directly and indirectly more than 5000 people, improving their livelihood.

Strategic Objective
Increase the number of beneficiaries in rural areas, funding agricultural and commercial services, while improving TA and monitoring business implementation by beneficiaries.

Note: the project will also try to link these small enterprises with the other ASN bank funded project on Fair Trade, by supporting activities that intends to add value (but not exclusively) onproduction of sesame, cashew nuts and peanuts.

To achieve this, the project will implement the following activities:
o Support CCMN on institutional development and its capacity to provide credit (liquidity);
o Promote extension and up scaling of existing projects, especially on agricultural projects (Sesame, Peanuts and Cashew nuts) ;
o Develop a fundraing plan for CCMN to increase its liquidity;
o Training CCMN staff to assist beneficiaries on project design, implementation and monitoring;
o Train beneficiaries on business management.

Geographic Areaand Beneficiaries
This project will be based in Nampula province and the idea is to focus into the same beneficiaries from a Fair Trade Project also funded ASN Bank and implemented by a local partner named AENA. The main goal, will be to increase commercialization of agricultural crops supported by AENA (Sesame, Cashew nuts and Peanuts), but also to have an intervention on the value chain development of this crops.
